Note:
you can set an alias for "kubectl" as:
alias k=kubectl

1. Deploy a pod call nginxpod with image nginx in controlplane, Make sure pod is not scheduled in worker node.
	k run nginxpod --image=nginx --dry-run=client -o yaml > 1.yaml

	edit 1.yaml
	nodeName: master <- insert this under spec

	k apply -f 1.yaml

	check the Node column:
	k get pod -o wide

2. Expose a existing pod called nginxpod a as service, service name should be nginxsvc. Pod port=80
	 k expose pod nginxpod --name=nginxsvc --port=80

3. Expose a existing pod called nginxpod, service name as nginxnodeportsvc, service should acces through NodePort (NodePort=30200)


### For Debugging
1. kubernetes logs <NAME>
2. k exec -it <POD_NAME> -- bin/bash     --> get inside the pod